is my yr old going through a stage do most yr olds go thru a naughty stage my yr old son is absolutely disobediant he is driving me crazy i just had a baby months ago and i find myself yelling at my yr old all the time and i know it is not good for my baby my yr old doesn't listen he argues and he yells i have used time outs taken away toys taken away priviledges and spanked him nothing works i am at the end of my rope i need some advise please help me sounds like your son is craving attention from you i am a kinder teacher and i have found that kids love attention and your child is trying to tell you hey mom look at me when he starts misbehaving he knows that you are going to give him some attention he is trying to test your limits don't give in be specific when you give him directions for instance you say he yells tell him that it is important not to yell in the house and make sure to model good behavior you are not teaching him any better by yelling back at him when you put him in time out make it minutes or less if he gets out of time out remind him that you will be adding more minutes when you take away his toys be consistent remind him that he must earn his toys back examples listening in the store helping with the baby make your son a big helper and have him help you with the baby when he does tell him what a great job he is doing and he will earn more privileges kids are smarter than we think be consistent model and only respond to good behavior just think i can handle a class full of year olds one is a piece of cake take care Dog training Child time-out Kodocha Bart chalkboard gags Codename: Kids Next Door Shaggy dog story Spanking EastEnders Recurring South Park characters Doug Springfield Elementary School The Marshall Mathers LP Episodes of Lost (Season 1) RuneScape quests Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Ron and Fez Baby Blues The McGuire Sisters The Life and Times of Juniper Lee President (game) Silent Night, Deadly Night Humphrey Bogart A